======================================================================
ANALYSIS: WHY |delta|=10 IS MISSING AT n=5
======================================================================

  H values at n=5: [1, 3, 5, 9, 11, 13, 15]
  For |delta|=10, need pairs (h, h+10):
    (1, 11): both exist, connected by flip? False
    (3, 13): both exist, connected by flip? False
    (5, 15): both exist, connected by flip? False
    (9, 19): 19 not achievable
    (11, 21): 21 not achievable
    (13, 23): 23 not achievable
    (15, 25): 25 not achievable

  Analysis of potentially reachable pairs:

  A single arc flip in n=5 affects:
    - Exactly 3 triangles (the ones containing the flipped arc)
    - The 5-cycle (if it uses the flipped arc)
    Each triangle can contribute ｱ1 to c3_directed
    The 5-cycle can contribute ｱ1 to c5_directed
    So max |delta(alpha_1)| <= 3 + 1 = 4 for 3-cycles + 5-cycles
    But also alpha_2 can change

  (delta_alpha_1, delta_alpha_2) distribution at n=5:
    (da1, da2): count
    (-6, +0):    20  => delta_H = -12
    (-4, +0):   180  => delta_H =  -8
    (-3, +0):   300  => delta_H =  -6
